def: The enacting or passing of a law a second time; the renewal ofa law.
The opening from the pharynx into the larynx or into thetrachea. See Larynx.
The state of being a landlord; the characteristics of alandlord; specifically, in Great Britain, the relation of landlordsto tenants, especially as regards leased agricultural lands. J. S.Mill.
That departnent of historical theology which treats of thelives and doctrines of the Fathers of the church.
A flaming, roundish body shot into the air; a case filled withcombustibles intended to burst and give light or set fire, or toproduce smoke or stench; as, a fire ball; a stink ball.
of or pertaining to a nephridium.
A keeper of stock or cattle; a herdsman. [Southwestern U. S.]Bartlett.
A narrow dale; a small dell; a small, secluded, and emboweredvalley.
